==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equipollency
<hw>E`qui*pol"len*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧quipollence</ets>. See <er>Equipollent</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Equality of power, force, signification, or
application.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>Sameness of signification of two
or more propositions which differ in language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equipollent</ent>⟦br⟧
